  "batch": "Cross-cutting Sweep",
  "batch_index": 3,
  "assessments": {
    "error_consistency": 82.0
  },
  "dimension_notes": {
    "error_consistency": {
      "evidence": [
        "Multiple orchestration/lifecycle paths discard errors from container-status/lookup calls and continue as if no container exists, which changes outcome from explicit failure to silent recovery attempts.",
        "In leak broadcast state update, serialization failures are logged but treated as a successful no-error return, so callers cannot distinguish successful state mutation from partial failure."
      ],
      "impact_scope": "subsystem",
      "fix_scope": "multi_file_refactor",
      "confidence": "high"
    }
  },
  "findings": [
    {
      "dimension": "error_consistency",
      "identifier": "container-lookup-failure-swallowed",
      "summary": "Decision points ignore container lookup errors and proceed as if conditions are healthy.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/docker/lifecycle/lifecycle.go",
        "goseg/docker/orchestration/minio.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`ensureRunningContainer` uses `existingContainer, _ := FindContainer(plan.Name)` and treats any non-nil error as `nil` state in the switch, skipping the failure signal and potentially creating/starting containers via blind recovery.",
        "`cleanupMinIOContainerForStart` also uses `existingContainer, _ := FindContainer(containerName)` and proceeds only on pointer nil, so lookup failures can hide and cause unnecessary delete/start attempts.",
        "`setMinIOAdminAccountWithRuntime` polls `status, _ := rt.getContainerRunningStatus(\"mc\")` and ignores errors, so transient Docker API failures can turn into indefinite waiting loops."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Capture and handle these lookup errors explicitly: return/publish a failure path when status/container queries fail, and only retry on explicit transient classes with bounded backoff. In polling loops, add timeout/circuit-breaker and fail with a surfaced operational error instead of looping forever.",
      "confidence": "high",
      "impact_scope": "subsystem",
      "fix_scope": "multi_file_refactor",
      "root_cause_cluster": "lookup-error-swallowing"
    },
    {
      "dimension": "error_consistency",
      "identifier": "marshal-failure-misreported-success",
      "summary": "Broadcast update returns success when payload marshal fails, masking mutation failure.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/leak/broadcast.go",
        "goseg/leak/broadcast_test.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`updateBroadcast` logs `json.Marshal(newBroadcast)` errors and returns `oldBroadcast, nil` rather than propagating an error.",
        "`updateBroadcast` also checks per-recipient `wrapperUrbitBytes, err := json.Marshal(wrappedUrbit)` and only sends on nil, but never returns/report this failure to callers.",
        "Tests in `goseg/leak/broadcast_test.go` validate `updateBroadcast` error behavior but do not observe partial-failure telemetry when marshalling fails, so this silent path is unobservable to callers."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Return a wrapped error when either marshal fails, and keep the function output explicit about failed updates (e.g., return unchanged state + error). Also propagate/aggregate per-recipient marshal failures so broadcast callers can react or alert on partial fanout failure.",
      "confidence": "high",
      "impact_scope": "module",
      "fix_scope": "single_edit",
      "root_cause_cluster": "lookup-error-swallowing"
    }
  ],
  "retrospective": {
    "root_causes": [
      "Error swallowing at decision boundaries in orchestration and broadcast paths creates false success states and hides recoverability signals.",
      "Inconsistent return conventions across paths that have clear failure modes (lookup failures/payload serialization failures) reduce observability and make retries or fallback logic unreliable."
    ],
    "likely_symptoms": [
      "Indefinite wait loops in MC/MinIO setup when Docker state queries fail.",
      "Silent partial-state divergence between expected and broadcasted leak notifications after marshal errors."
    ],
    "possible_false_positives": []
  }
}


